  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2236",
  "title": "Make V2 the default homepage?",
  "body": "V2 is officially out. Should we make the https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/ homepage the V2 one and then display a banner for V1 docs (or just a top menu item so it's less intrusive)?\r\n\r\nIt's not a big priority. But could still be confusing for newcomers searching for InstantSearch.js and ending up on the V1 website.\r\nIt's very easy to dismiss a banner because it looks a bit like an ad (\"This website use cookies...\" effect)\r\n\r\nThe hierarchy could be:\r\n- / => V2 homepage\r\n- /v2/* v2 docs\r\n- /* others, v1 docs (so there's no need to handle 301 etc. for now)\r\n\r\nThe goal being to push V2 even more.",
